      "text": "JavaScript HTML DOM Document"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The HTML DOM document object is the owner of all other objects in your web page."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "The HTML DOM Document Object"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The document object represents your web page."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you want to access any element in an HTML page, you always start with accessing the \ndocument object."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Below are some examples of how you can use the document object to access and \nmanipulate HTML."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Finding HTML Elements"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Method",
          "Description"
        ],
        [
          "document.getElementById(id)",
          "Find an element by element id"
        ],
        [
          "document.getElementsByTagName(name)",
          "Find elements by tag name"
        ],
        [
          "document.getElementsByClassName(name)",
          "Find elements by class name"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
